description: This system performs repository analysis by orchestrating static code scanning, semantic AI-based interpretation, and incremental diagram/document synthesis. The Core Orchestrator coordinates scanning and change detection, which the Static Analysis Engine converts into structural graphs and persistent state. An AI Agentic System interprets that structural data to produce logical component groupings and narratives. The Incremental Synthesis Engine generates and updates Mermaid diagrams and manifests based on agent outputs and impact analysis. Documentation & Visualization render final outputs (Markdown/HTML/interactive diagrams), while Code Health & Diagnostics compute architectural metrics. Infrastructure & Persistence provide telemetry, caching, and storage to support incremental, cost-efficient operation.

components.name: Core Orchestrator
components.description: Central command layer managing job lifecycle, CLI entry, plugin discovery, configuration, and repository change detection; coordinates scanning, analysis, and synthesis.

components.name: CLI & Execution Controller
components.description: Primary entry point and supervisor for the application. Validates user arguments, manages high-level execution flow, and coordinates the lifecycle of analysis jobs.

components.name: Repository & Change Manager
components.description: Handles repository lifecycle tasks and detects incremental changes between runs. Filters relevant files using ignore patterns to optimize scanning and determines which files require fresh analysis.

components.name: Environment & Plugin Registry
components.description: Manages the discovery and installation of external tooling (LSP servers, analyzers) and provides a generic registry to load language-specific scanners and LLM providers dynamically.

components.name: AI Orchestration & Schema
components.description: Configures the AI layer and enforces structured analysis schemas. Coordinates between the orchestrator and specialized LLM agents to ensure reliable synthesis of documentation and diagrams.

components.name: Static Analysis Engine
components.description: Extracts structural ground-truth from the codebase using LSP clients and language-specific scanners, building and persisting a graph-based state for incremental updates.

components.name: Orchestration & API Facade
components.description: Central controller and primary entry point for the static analysis subsystem; manages high-level workflow, incremental update logic, and coordinates scanning, LSP interaction, and graph construction.

components.name: Project Discovery & Environment
components.description: Scans the filesystem to identify source files, determines primary project languages, discovers external dependencies, and provides configuration context for initializing appropriate LSP servers.

components.name: LSP Client Infrastructure
components.description: Manages lifecycle and communication with language servers over JSON-RPC, performs queries (e.g., find-definitions, find-references), and bootstraps language-specific environments.

components.name: Graph Modeling & Analysis
components.description: Transforms symbol and reference data into a navigable call graph, creating nodes for code entities and edges for invocations/dependencies, and applies clustering to group related nodes into hierarchical abstractions.

components.name: Persistence & State Management
components.description: Handles serialization and storage of analysis results and metadata to disk, enabling incremental analysis by providing baseline states and caching to minimize redundant processing.

components.name: AI Agentic System
components.description: Multi-agent layer that semantically interprets static analysis data using deterministic planning and specialized agents (Abstraction, Details, Meta) and a Toolkit for code inspection and grouping.

components.name: Agent Orchestration & Planning
components.description: Provides the foundational execution environment for agents, including LLM client management and deterministic logic that decides which code components require further semantic expansion based on previous analysis results.

components.name: Specialized Analysis Agents
components.description: Task-specific agents implementing different analysis strategies: AbstractionAgent groups components into logical clusters, DetailsAgent analyzes implementation details, and MetaAgent provides project-wide context.

components.name: Agentic Toolkit
components.description: An extensible collection of tools that interface with the repository and static analysis results, allowing agents to programmatically query the codebase's structure, behavior, and history.

components.name: Prompt & Schema Management
components.description: Manages LLM prompt construction across providers and defines structured Pydantic schemas to ensure deterministic, parsable LLM outputs ready for downstream synthesis.

components.name: Incremental Synthesis Engine
components.description: Generates and maintains Mermaid.js diagrams incrementally, performing impact analysis to update only affected diagram parts based on code changes.

components.name: Synthesis Orchestration & State
components.description: Manages the high-level execution flow and persistent analysis state (the AnalysisManifest). Decides between full builds and incremental updates, loads/saves sub-analysis results, and ensures the final Mermaid output reflects the current manifest.

components.name: Impact Analysis Engine
components.description: Translates filesystem changes (adds, deletes, modifications) into architectural impacts by mapping changed file paths to logical components and detecting cross-boundary effects that require re-generation of dependent or parent component diagrams.

components.name: Incremental Update Controller
components.description: Central execution logic for the incremental workflow: receives dirty components from the Impact Analysis Engine, patches moved file paths, removes deleted entities, and coordinates re-analysis of modified code, bridging orchestration and analysis workers.

components.name: Semantic Abstraction & Validation
components.description: AI-driven abstraction and validation layer that interprets code structure and generates high-level summaries. Combines agent-based semantic abstraction with static-analysis primitives (package relations, call graphs) to validate and refresh component summaries for affected clusters.

components.name: Documentation & Visualization
components.description: Transforms internal analysis models into user-facing formats (Markdown, MDX, HTML) and renders interactive visualizations using Cytoscape and Mermaid.js templates.

components.name: Analysis Model Transformer
components.description: Converts raw analysis outputs into a consistent UnifiedAnalysisJson schema, flattening or nesting hierarchical component data and preparing component metadata for downstream generators.

components.name: Static Document Engine
components.description: Generates static, version-control-friendly documentation (Markdown and MDX) and embeds Mermaid.js diagrams and source links to represent components and relations in text formats.

components.name: Interactive Visualization Engine
components.description: Produces interactive HTML/Cytoscape.js visualizations and Sphinx-compatible assets, mapping the unified analysis model into graph data structures and templates for in-browser exploration.

components.name: Documentation Orchestrator
components.description: Central controller that coordinates generator execution, normalizes repository context (git hashes, branches, paths), and triggers documentation builds based on configuration or CI/CD events.

components.name: Code Health Analyzer
components.description: Runs language-specific checks and aggregates maintainability metrics (e.g., circular dependencies, cohesion) into a health report that is embedded in the documentation metadata.

components.name: Code Health & Diagnostics
components.description: Diagnostic suite computing architectural health metrics (coupling, cohesion, instability), detecting smells, and producing reports integrated into documentation.

components.name: Metric & Smell Detectors
components.description: Implements diagnostic logic that computes metrics (coupling, cohesion, instability) and detects structural smells/anti-patterns like deep inheritance, circular dependencies, and God Classes.

components.name: Health Reporting & Aggregation
components.description: Defines schemas and models for representing health data and aggregates individual check results into a comprehensive HealthReport used for documentation and incremental updates.

components.name: Incremental Impact Analysis
components.description: Analyzes changes between repository states to determine how code edits affect architectural boundaries and whether they introduce instability or cross-component leakage, enabling incremental updates to reports.

components.name: Architectural Topology & Resolution
components.description: Maps raw code entities (files, methods) to logical components, handles path normalization and reference resolution, and validates the resulting topology used by detectors and impact analysis.

components.name: Infrastructure & Persistence
components.description: Provides monitoring, logging, caching, telemetry, LLM token tracking, and job state persistence (e.g., DuckDB and file caches) to support incremental operation and cost control.

components.name: Incremental Cache Manager
components.description: Manages the lifecycle of cached analysis results using file- and prompt-level fingerprinting to detect staleness and skip redundant LLM operations, reducing cost and processing time.

components.name: Telemetry & Instrumentation Engine
components.description: Instruments the agentic workflow to capture execution traces, LLM token usage, and cost metrics via decorators, context managers, and callbacks to enable monitoring and debugging of non-deterministic LLM behavior.

components.name: Job Persistence Layer
components.description: Stores structured analysis job records and metadata using DuckDB to enable session recovery, historical analysis, and relational queries over repository processing tasks.
